<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[310,1181,2168,2760]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
DESCRIPTION.—Form (
<figureCitation box="[731,900,2442,2479]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="27.[309,402,1870,1901]" captionTargetBox="[300,1166,514,1841]" captionText="FIGURE 43.—Habitus of Xystosomus microtretus, male, Hamburg Farm, Costa Rica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828559/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Figure 43</figureCitation>
): Medium-sized, broad, moderately convex (more so than 
<emphasis box="[1018,1181,2488,2524]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[1018,1161,2488,2524]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gruti">X. gruti</taxonomicName>
),
</emphasis>
with small flat eyes, narrow head, broad pronotum, and square humeri. Easily distinguished from the other species of the group (see below) by the form of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[310,1181,2168,2760]" lastBlockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[353,463,2718,2754]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Color:</emphasis>
Head and body rufopiceous; pronotum and elytra moderately iridescent; appendages 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2018,2102,1200,1237]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">testaceous</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Head: Very broad between eyes; frontal furrows shallowly impressed posterior to clypeus, not prolonged onto frons beyond anterior margin of eye; eyes small, slightly prominent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[1276,1441,1475,1511]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Pronotum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1492,1679,1475,1512]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="27.[309,402,1870,1901]" captionTargetBox="[300,1166,514,1841]" captionText="FIGURE 43.—Habitus of Xystosomus microtretus, male, Hamburg Farm, Costa Rica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828559/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Figure 43</figureCitation>
): 
<emphasis box="[1730,1910,1475,1512]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Transverse</emphasis>
(W/ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2018,2104,1475,1512]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">L, x</emphasis>
1.58; range, 1.53-1.68; 3 specimens); lateral setigerous pores present only at hind angles; laterobasal carinae rudimentary; hind angles about 90°, sides anterior to angles more or less straight; side 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2030,2107,1658,1695]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">margins</emphasis>
beaded, not reflexed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[1280,1397,1750,1786]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Elytra:</emphasis>
Each elytron with six rows of partially striate serial punctures and punctulae, rows 2-6 effaced before apex; side margins narrowly explanate; humeral projection absent, humerus evenly rounded; chaetotaxy as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1730,1875,1933,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gruti">
<emphasis box="[1730,1767,1933,1970]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">X</emphasis>
. gruti
</taxonomicName>
; plica short, evident externally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" box="[1283,1824,2026,2063]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[1283,1551,2026,2062]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Microsculpture:</emphasis>
As in 
<taxonomicName box="[1676,1819,2026,2063]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gruti">
X. 
<emphasis box="[1734,1819,2026,2062]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">gruti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1819,1824,2026,2062]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[1283,1811,2072,2108]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Secondary sexual characters:</emphasis>
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1427,2117,2154]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="28.[299,391,1507,1538]" captionTargetBox="[296,1119,408,1438]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 45.—Male genitalia, left lateral aspect, of Xystosomus microtretus, Hamburg Farm, Costa Rica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828561" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828561/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Figure 45</figureCitation>
) with internal sac quite different than in members of other species groups. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1510,2209,2246]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="28.[1238,1329,1884,1915]" captionTargetBox="[1208,2100,489,1853]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 46.—Female genitalia, ventral aspect, with spermathecal reservoir, of Xystosomus microtretus, Hamburg Farm, Costa Rica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828563/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Figure 46</figureCitation>
) characteristic of the species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[1238,2113,1200,2762]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[1285,1365,2256,2292]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">Size:</emphasis>
Three specimens: length, 3.3-3.6 mm; width, 1.6-1.7 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1486,1560,2302,2339]" pageId="27" pageNumber="24">mm.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
